    public class Individual
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<Individual>
    An Individual is a Resource with an associated Model. Given an Individual one can query or update properties that have that individual as their subject. This is not the case with a Resource, because a Resource object has no model associated with it. The Individual class is the base class for the Java classes generated by Hedwig that correspond to OWL classes.
    See Also:
    Resource, Model, Serialized Form
